      "question": "If $3 \\cot \\theta = 2$, find the value of $\\frac{4 \\sin \\theta - 3 \\cos \\theta}{2 \\sin \\theta + 6 \\cos \\theta}$.",
      "answer": "\\frac{1}{3}",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Given $3 \\cot \\theta = 2$, so $\\cot \\theta = \\frac{2}{3} = \\frac{\\cos \\theta}{\\sin \\theta}$.",
          "Divide numerator and denominator of the expression by $\\sin \\theta$ to get $\\frac{4 - 3 \\cot \\theta}{2 + 6 \\cot \\theta}$.",
          "Substitute $\\cot \\theta = \\frac{2}{3}$ and simplify."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\frac{4 \\sin \\theta - 3 \\cos \\theta}{2 \\sin \\theta + 6 \\cos \\theta} = \\frac{4 - 3 \\cot \\theta}{2 + 6 \\cot \\theta} = \\frac{4 - 3(2/3)}{2 + 6(2/3)} = \\frac{4-2}{2+4} = \\frac{2}{6} = \\frac{1}{3}"
      },
