      "question": "Evaluate $\\frac{\\cos 45^\\circ}{\\sec 30^\\circ + \\text{cosec } 30^\\circ}$.",
      "answer": "\\frac{3\\sqrt{2} - \\sqrt{6}}{8}",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Substitute the standard values: $\\cos 45^\\circ = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}}$, $\\sec 30^\\circ = \\frac{2}{\\sqrt{3}}$, and $\\text{cosec } 30^\\circ = 2$.",
          "Simplify the denominator and rationalize the expression."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\frac{1/\\sqrt{2}}{2/\\sqrt{3} + 2} = \\frac{1/\\sqrt{2}}{(2 + 2\\sqrt{3})/\\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{\\sqrt{2}(2+2\\sqrt{3})} = \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2\\sqrt{2} + 2\\sqrt{6}} = \\frac{\\sqrt{3}(2\\sqrt{6} - 2\\sqrt{2})}{8 - 24} = \\frac{2\\sqrt{18} - 2\\sqrt{6}}{16} = \\frac{6\\sqrt{2} - 2\\sqrt{6}}{16} = \\frac{3\\sqrt{2} - \\sqrt{6}}{8}"
      },
